commentary: Lyon to Imam-ul-Haq, no run and big spin this time! In fact, there's an appeal - though not a very expansive one as Australia think he's edged it to Carey - and Michael Gough's finger shoots up! Imam doesn't think he's hit it, and sends it upstairs, reviewing. Gosh, replays show a massive gap between the ball and the bat, that's definitely not out, and the decision is over-turned. The bat might have hit the pad, which is what the on-field umpire heard

commentary: Behrendorff to Umar Akmal, OUT caught in the deep! Just as the stand was starting to grow, Umar has tried to force the issue, skipping down the track and dragging a loft into the leg side. But he doesn't get all of it, and Cummins moves quickly to his left at deep midwicket, sliding to hold the catch

commentary: Zampa to Mohammad Hasnain, OUT there's a review. Zampa floats a googly up high and it rushes in to beat Hasnain's inside edge and hit him on the back leg. The appeal is turned down, but they ask for a review. Three reds, and he's gone!
